Tharina Human, Pieter Jacobus van Zyl and Laetitia Nel, the three people accused of kidnapping 6-year-old Amy’Leigh de Jager outside her school, will continue with their bail application in the Vanderbijlpark Magistrate's Court on Tuesday. JOHANNESBURG - On Tuesday, three people accused of kidnapping six-year-old Amy’Leigh de Jager are expected to find out whether they will be going back home. READ: Amy'Leigh kidnapping suspects' bail application continues The trio, including a teacher, have spent almost a month behind bars after the crime in early September. READ: Fourth suspect in Amy'Leigh kidnapping to appear in court They have applied for bail in the Vanderbijlpark Magistrate’s Court and are expected to find out from the presiding officer whether they can go back into the public. The state in the case is opposing bail, saying all three accused are very close to witnesses and could manipulate the case.